  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is correct. The given equation is quadratic. The maximum value of a function defined by a quadratic equation can be displayed as a constant in the vertex form of the equation, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals a left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus k\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>k</mi></math>, where the maximum value of the function is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math>, which occurs when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals h\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>h</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\"><mi>a</mi></math> is a constant. The given equation can be rewritten in this form by completing the square. To complete the square, the given equation can be rewritten as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 6 left parenthesis x squared minus 10 x right parenthesis minus 126\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>126</mn></math>, which is equivalent to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 6 left parenthesis x squared minus 10 x plus 25 right parenthesis minus 126 plus 6 left parenthesis 25 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>126</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 6 left parenthesis x minus 5 right parenthesis squared plus 24\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn></math>. This equation is in vertex form, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a equals negative 6\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h equals 5\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k equals 24\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></math>. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals minus 6 left parenthesis x minus 5 right parenthesis squared plus 24\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><msup><mo>)</mo><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>24</mn></math> displays the maximum value, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"24\"><mn>24</mn></math>, of the function as a constant.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect. This form displays one of the zeros, not the maximum value, of the function as a constant.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect. This form displays the zeros, not the maximum value, of the function as constants.</p>",
